From a106b5c9b3420677d0a5a2def2962b2c8b06e36b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 16:37:32 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 30/44] inline-3d(#625): restore the renderer's eye feed in
 sync-weave mode + scope views to the scene element
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The inline-3d session has been silently serving its MONO fallback — one view
at the origin, symmetric projection — so a rendered scene showed no cube (it
sits at z=0, i.e. exactly at the camera, and is clipped) and no look-around.
Confirmed live: getViewerPose().views == 1, eye "none", pos [0,0,0], no
frustum skew.

Root cause: XRSession::UpdateInline3DViews is gated on
inline_3d_eyes_valid_ && rect_valid, which come from
DisplayXRService::GetLatestEyes -> the BROWSER process's weave-client cache.
That cache is only ever written by a weave submit (SubmitWin /
SubmitBatchWin) — and since the sync-weave move (#625) the submits happen in
the GPU process, so the browser's cache is never populated and the gate never
opens. Dropping the async mojo WeaveSubmit path removed the only channel that
carried eyes back to the browser; the scene path has been dead since (which
is why hello-cube's look-around was never validated).

- mojom DisplayXRWeaver gains ReportInline3DEyes(eyes, valid), fire-and-forget
  GPU->browser; DisplayXRWeaveGpu pushes after every sync submit (single and
  batch); DisplayXRWeaverImpl seeds the browser cache via
  DisplayXRWeaveClient::SetEyesFromGpu. The remote is already bound in sync
  mode (ShellContentGpuClient), so this needs no new plumbing.
- mojom DisplayXRService::GetLatestEyes now takes the caller's
  element_window_rect: the browser only knows the LAST SUBMITTED weave rect,
  which on a page with several 3D windows is an arbitrary element — building
  the scene's frustum from a photo's rect puts it in the wrong place at the
  wrong scale. XRSession tracks the scene layer (the one carrying
  virtualDisplayHeight) and sends its canvas rect, on the same
  window-relative device-px basis ReportInline3DRects uses. Empty rect => the
  old submitted-rect behavior (single-window pages).

With the feed restored, tag+29's virtualDisplayHeight (display-rig m2v) stops
being dead code and actually scales the eye poses.
